http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/Contest-to-mark-Teachers-Day/article14596123.ece

The Hindu In School, in association with Camlin Kokuyo, is organising a contest to mark Teachers Day. Students will get a chance to write a 50-word note on the topic ‘A teacher who made a difference to my life.’The note, which should be written using a pen on paper and then scanned, should be mailed tocamlinteachersdaycontest@thehindu.co.inalong with a passport size photograph of the student.The student’s name, class, school, and city should be mentioned on the scanned copy of the note and in the e-mail.The size of the attachment should not exceed 2MB.The last day for sending the entries is September 5, 2016.